      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Cyclopropanone is highly reactive because of its large amount of angle strain. Methylcyclopropenone, although even more strained than cyclopropanone, is nevertheless quite stable and can even be distilled. Explain, taking the polarity of the carbonyl group into account.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBamdWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--34efb0f11c2ac1a681ce9e366a5d5edf4396458f/OChem_15_EC_011.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclopropanone has a 3-carbon ring. C 1 is a carbonyl group. Methylcyclopropenone has a cyclopropene ring. C 1 is a carbonyl group and C2 is bonded to a methyl group.\">",
